# Self Join (Frequently Asked)

Same table joined with itself.

### Employee Table

| emp_id | name  | manager_id |
| ------ | ----- | ---------- |
| 1      | John  | NULL       |
| 2      | Mary  | 1          |
| 3      | David | 1          |
| 4      | Sara  | 2          |

---

### Find Employee and Manager

```sql
SELECT e.name AS employee,
       m.name AS manager
FROM employee e
LEFT JOIN employee m
ON e.manager_id = m.emp_id;
```

### Output

| Employee | Manager |
| -------- | ------- |
| John     | NULL    |
| Mary     | John    |
| David    | John    |
| Sara     | Mary    |

---

# CPDSS-Based Join Example

Suppose:

### vessel

| vessel_id | vessel_name |
| --------- | ----------- |
| 1         | MT Alpha    |

### voyage

| voyage_id | vessel_id |
| --------- | --------- |
| 1001      | 1         |

---

### Fetch Vessel Name and Voyage

```sql
SELECT v.vessel_name,
       vg.voyage_id
FROM vessel v
INNER JOIN voyage vg
ON v.vessel_id = vg.vessel_id;
```

